   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Fifty-three SIN REIGNED Scripture: Rom 5:21 The meaning of sin Sin is not only a behavior but also a life.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Sin is not a dead thing but a living being with a personality.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Sin itself is the life of the Devil, Satan.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The behavior of sin is the multitude of wicked things.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The power of sin The behavior of sin causes man to suffer punishment of sin, and sin itself is a kind of power dwelling in man.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The power of sin dominates man and puts man under the slavery of sin; thus sin can reign in man.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The result of the reigning of sin It causes man to sin and do evil against his will.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>It causes man to die.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Once man sins and does evil, he has to die.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>How to escape sin</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Develop this point.</S>
   </TEXT>
